RESOLVED_ENTITIES.the first factor: first factor in determining voluntariness of consent

AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.first factor in determining voluntarines: factor weighing against the United States due to temporary detention for a traffic violation and increasing suspicions of drug trafficking
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Williamson County Sheriff's Office: Law enforcement agency conducting the search and requesting consent from Federico Saldana
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.Federico Saldana: Defendant in the case, driver of the 2008 Chevrolet truck, gave consent to Williamson County Sheriff's Office to search the vehicle and trailer, identified himself during the traffic stop, served 9 years in federal prison, contended that officers' prolonged detention exceeded the scope of the reason for the traffic stop
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.United States Government: Party responding to Federico Saldana's motion, arguing that consent to search was voluntary
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.traffic violation: Reason for initial detention of Federico Saldana, unsafe lane changes and near-collisions
AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.suspicions of drug trafficking: Reason for continued investigation and search, based on atypical features of the 2008 Chevrolet truck and flatbed trailer
